This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Obama and Prime Minister Abe of Japan before their bilateral meeting. Prime Minister Abe expresses gratitude for the assistance provided by the United States after the East Japan earthquake. He emphasizes the importance of the alliance between Japan and the United States and their shared values and strategic interests. President Obama thanks the Prime Minister for the hospitality and agrees that the U.S.-Japan alliance is crucial for security in the Asia Pacific region. They discuss the challenges posed by North Korea and the need to work together on economic, diplomatic, and cultural issues. Both leaders express confidence in the continued strength of the friendship and alliance between their countries.